PART III — UNIVERSAL TEAM ALIGNMENT MATRIX (THE 4 PILLARS)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

This matrix establishes the single source of truth across all organizational
layers. The agent MUST evaluate every generated module against ALL four pillars
simultaneously.

[PILLAR 1: VISUAL & AESTHETIC — FOR DESIGNERS & FRONTEND]
  - Cinematic Dark Aesthetic: Strict adherence to chiaroscuro lighting and
    micro-interactions.
  - Absolute Responsive Laws: Zero horizontal overflow at 375px, 768px, and
    1440px. No exceptions.
  - Memory & Lifecycle: AudioContext and WebGL meshes MUST be strictly suspended
    and disposed of when off-screen or inactive to prevent GPU/memory drain.

[PILLAR 2: DETERMINISTIC ENGINEERING — FOR BACKEND & DEVOPS]
  - Database Performance: PostgreSQL SELECT 1 execution time MUST be < 50ms.
  - Cache/Queue Performance: Redis PING response time MUST be < 10ms.
  - Orchestration Sequence: Nginx gateway ONLY opens after Database is healthy
    AND Drizzle migrations succeed.
  - Environment Isolation: Native ffmpeg, Python 3, and yt-dlp run strictly
    containerized.

[PILLAR 3: THE FINALIZATION CONTRACT — FOR QA & PRODUCT OWNERS]
  Deployment Readiness: A feature is 100% complete ONLY when:
    1. TypeScript strict mode passes with zero errors.
    2. ESLint has ZERO warnings or errors.
    3. Lighthouse performance, accessibility, and best practices scores >= 95.
    4. Playwright End-to-End testing matrix passes unconditionally.

[PILLAR 4: SYSTEM VISIBILITY — FOR STAKEHOLDERS]
  - Real-Time Health: The /api/health endpoint MUST continuously expose
    real-time metrics for PostgreSQL, Redis, BullMQ, and AWS S3 status,
    ensuring total transparency for business operations.

