PART VIII — FINALIZATION CONTRACT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The repository is not considered complete unless ALL of the following conditions
are satisfied simultaneously:

  - TypeScript strict mode passes with zero errors
  - ESLint passes with zero warnings
  - Production build succeeds
  - Zero unresolved imports
  - Zero runtime crashes
  - Zero hydration mismatches
  - Zero React warnings
  - Zero console errors
  - Zero memory leaks detected
  - Lighthouse Performance score >= 90 on all devices
  - Lighthouse Accessibility score >= 95
  - Lighthouse Best Practices score >= 95
  - Lighthouse SEO score >= 90
  - Mobile responsiveness verified on all breakpoints
  - API routes verified against OpenAPI spec
  - OpenAPI schema validated
  - Database migrations verified
  - Environment validation verified
  - Redis connectivity verified
  - PostgreSQL connectivity verified
  - S3 upload pipeline verified
  - JWT authentication verified
  - AI retry logic verified
  - WebGL GPU cleanup verified
  - AudioContext lifecycle verified

The agent MUST NOT claim completion before all verification passes.
WHEN IN DOUBT, FOLLOW THE EXISTING REPOSITORY ARCHITECTURE.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART IX — GLOBAL EXECUTION CONTRACT — NON-NEGOTIABLE RUNTIME LAWS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The agent MUST obey the following laws globally across ALL prompts, ALL files,
and ALL generated output:

  LAW 01: NEVER invent alternative architectures. The architecture defined in
          this document is mandatory and immutable.

  LAW 02: NEVER rename files, folders, exports, interfaces, routes, database
          columns, hooks, contexts, components, or services unless explicitly
          instructed.

  LAW 03: NEVER omit imports, exports, typings, env references, middleware
          bindings, providers, listeners, cleanup handlers, error boundaries,
          loading states, or fallback states.

  LAW 04: EVERY generated file MUST be immediately runtime-compatible with
          all previously generated files.

  LAW 05: The system MUST remain compile-safe after EVERY prompt.

  LAW 06: If dependencies are missing: install them, update package.json,
          regenerate lockfile, and verify compatibility before continuing.

  LAW 07: NEVER output pseudo-code.

  LAW 08: NEVER summarize implementation logic.

  LAW 09: NEVER say: "implement similarly", "standard setup", "same as above",
          "placeholder", "example", "TODO", "mock later", "for brevity", or
          "// your code here".

  LAW 10: EVERY shell command MUST be executable exactly as written.

  LAW 11: EVERY generated module MUST include: imports, exports, strict
          TypeScript typing, error handling, cleanup logic, null safety.

  LAW 12: If runtime ambiguity exists: choose the most robust implementation.

  LAW 13: All generated code MUST pass TypeScript strict mode, ESLint, and
          production build before continuing to the next prompt.

  LAW 14: NEVER skip verification steps.

  LAW 15: After every prompt: run typecheck, run lint, run available tests,
          confirm zero runtime errors.

  LAW 16: The repository MUST remain deployable after every single step.

  LAW 17: All async operations MUST include: timeout handling, retry strategy,
          cancellation cleanup, and structured logging.

  LAW 18: All React components MUST: avoid memory leaks, cleanup listeners,
          cleanup animation frames, cleanup WebGL resources, cleanup audio
          nodes on unmount.

  LAW 19: ALL API routes MUST return deterministic response envelopes.

  LAW 20: Any missing implementation detail MUST be resolved using the existing
          architecture — never minimal or temporary implementations.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART X — SYSTEM RESILIENCE & SECURITY CONTRACTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[ENVIRONMENT VALIDATION CONTRACT]
  - The backend MUST fail-fast on missing env variables at startup.
  - Zod validation required at server boot. No process may start with
    undefined secrets.
  - All env values MUST be typed. .env.example MUST remain synchronized
    with actual env usage at all times.

[GLOBAL ERROR ARCHITECTURE]
  - All API errors MUST use structured JSON responses (ApiResponse<T>).
  - Unhandled promise rejections are forbidden anywhere in the codebase.
  - Global Express error middleware REQUIRED.
  - React Error Boundaries REQUIRED for all async UI regions.
  - All logs MUST include: timestamp, severity level, and module source.
  - Secrets MUST NEVER appear in logs or error messages.

[MANDATORY SECURITY HARDENING]
  - Helmet.js: mandatory on all Express routes.
  - CSRF protection: mandatory on all state-mutating routes.
  - Rate limiting: mandatory via Redis-backed express-rate-limit.
  - CORS: allowlist only — wildcard (*) is forbidden.
  - Cookies: secure flag in production, SameSite=strict required.
  - API key encryption at rest: mandatory (AES-256-GCM).
  - SQL injection prevention: parameterized queries only via Drizzle ORM.
  - XSS sanitization: required on all rich-text inputs.

[AI RESILIENCE CONTRACT]
  - All AI calls MUST implement exponential backoff retry (max 3 attempts,
    delays: 1s, 2s, 4s).
  - Timeout ceiling MUST be enforced on every external AI call.
  - Queue retry state MUST be persisted in Redis via BullMQ.
  - Failed jobs MUST resume safely after server restart.
  - AI service failure MUST NEVER crash the main application thread.

[MEDIA STORAGE CONTRACT]
  - All uploads MUST generate deterministic, collision-safe filenames.
  - MIME type validation REQUIRED on all uploaded files.
  - Maximum upload size MUST be enforced at middleware level.
  - Virus scanning integration point REQUIRED.
  - Temporary files MUST auto-delete after processing completes.
  - S3 paths MUST follow the structure: /{entity_type}/{entity_id}/{asset}.{ext}

[MONOREPO ENFORCEMENT]
  - Shared types MUST originate from one canonical source:
    artifacts/ace-2026/src/types/index.ts
  - Circular dependencies are forbidden.
  - Path aliases REQUIRED in all tsconfig files.
  - Absolute imports preferred over deep relative traversal.
  - All workspace packages MUST remain independently buildable.

[TEST ENFORCEMENT CONTRACT]
  - No feature is considered complete without tests.
  - Critical user paths require E2E Playwright coverage.
  - All API routes require integration tests.
  - All custom hooks require unit tests.
  - CI pipeline MUST fail below required coverage threshold.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XI — SECTION 0: ABSOLUTE LAWS (NON-NEGOTIABLE, NEVER OVERRIDE)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

LAW 1 — ZERO DUMMY DATA
  No Lorem Ipsum. No hardcoded images. No default styles tied to content.
  Every content field initializes as null. The site launches as a complete,
  error-free, intelligent shell. Content is born the moment the admin injects
  it through the CMS.

LAW 2 — NULL-FIRST STATE ARCHITECTURE
  Every variable — composer name, biography, portrait, audio tracks, social
  links, awards, studio address — initializes as null in frontend state.
  UI renders gracefully with null values: zero errors, zero broken layouts,
  zero console warnings. Null states display dark or ivory canvases depending
  on active theme. React Error Boundaries REQUIRED at route level.

LAW 3 — OMNI-LINGUAL DATABASE STRUCTURE
  Every text field in the database follows this mandatory structure:
    { en: "", es: "", fr: "", zh: "", ja: "", ko: "" }
  No text field may be limited to one language. Ever.
  CSS logical properties used throughout for RTL-readiness.
  All 6 languages are currently LTR. Architecture is RTL-ready with zero
  refactoring needed.

LAW 4 — INTELLIGENT SHELL LAUNCH
  At deploy time, the site is a fully functioning, error-free canvas. The
  composer activates it by injecting data through the admin panel.

LAW 5 — ENGLISH-ONLY CODE
  All code comments, variable names, function names, file names, and
  documentation must be in English only.

LAW 6 — STRICT PRODUCTION STANDARDS
  Every component shipped is final, polished, and production-ready. All
  shipped components must pass the Finalization Contract verification.

LAW 7 — PERFORMANCE IS NON-NEGOTIABLE
  Lighthouse Performance: >= 90 on all devices.
  First Contentful Paint: < 1.2 seconds.
  Time to Interactive: < 2.5 seconds.
  Largest Contentful Paint: < 2.5 seconds.
  Cumulative Layout Shift: < 0.1.
  60fps animations everywhere. No layout shifts.

LAW 8 — CROSS-PLATFORM PARITY
  Every feature works identically on iOS, Android, macOS, and Windows.
  Touch gestures on mobile. Mouse precision on desktop. No feature is
  desktop-only unless physically impossible on mobile.

LAW 9 — HYPER-REALISTIC DEMO SIMULATION MATRIX
  When the environment variable DEMO_MODE=true is active, the entire full-stack
  system MUST bypass live database writes, remote API dependencies, and external
  asset downloading.

  9.1: The frontend and mock controllers MUST seamlessly route multimedia asset
       requests to localized paths within the /public/ directory, specifically
       utilizing /public/audio/, /public/images/, and /public/videos/.

  9.2: All advanced AI operations (including auto-thumbnailing, dynamic captions,
       and instant multi-language translation across all 6 blueprint languages)
       MUST simulate high-performance real-time processing via elegant, stylized
       loading interfaces (< 2-3 seconds) and resolve immediately using
       ultra-realistic local mock data.

  9.3: The codebase architecture MUST maintain absolute dual-mode compatibility:
       the orchestration pipelines, API route schemas, and database mappings for
       the real-world deployment (Real Mode) MUST remain untouched and fully
       production-safe, while the local demo toggle safely routes data to ensure
       a 100% stable, offline-capable, cinematic presentation.

