    Double Exposure blend mode: 'overlay'
    Portrait treatment: black and white, sepia

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LANGUAGE-SPECIFIC FONT ARCHITECTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Applied on locale change in < 100ms:

  en: --font-display applied, letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing-base)
  es: same as en, line-height +5% for accent character clearance
  fr: same as en, line-height +5% for accent character clearance
  zh: 'Noto Sans SC', letter-spacing: 0.05em, line-height: var(--line-height-cjk)
  ja: 'Noto Sans JP', letter-spacing: 0.03em, line-height: var(--line-height-cjk)
  ko: 'Noto Sans KR', letter-spacing: 0.04em, line-height: var(--line-height-cjk)

All fonts loaded via Google Fonts with font-display: swap.
Preloaded in <head> for zero flash of unstyled text.

RTL SUPPORT:
  All 6 languages are LTR. CSS logical properties used throughout.
  RTL expansion requires zero refactoring.

CSS VARIABLE INJECTION PATTERN (exact implementation):

  const applyTheme = (theme: ThemeConfig, locale: Locale) => {
    const root = document.documentElement;
    Object.entries(theme.variables).forEach(([key, value]) => {
      root.style.setProperty(key, value);
    });
    root.setAttribute('data-theme', theme.id);
    root.setAttribute('data-locale', locale);
    root.setAttribute('lang', locale);
    root.setAttribute('dir', 'ltr');
    applyLocaleTypography(locale, theme);
  };

