PART XV — SECTION 3: LINGUISTIC PORTAL (THE GRAND ENTRY GATE)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SUPPORTED LANGUAGES:
  en — English  — "ENGLISH"
  es — Spanish  — "ESPANOL"
  fr — French   — "FRANCAIS"
  zh — Chinese  — "中文"
  ja — Japanese — "日本語"
  ko — Korean   — "한국어"

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VISUAL ARCHITECTURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Canvas: 100vw x 100vh, no scroll, no overflow.

Background Three.js scene:
  - 15,000 star particles (BufferGeometry points)
  - Slow Y-axis rotation: 0.00008 radians/frame
  - Depth fog: THREE.FogExp2 color #000000 density 0.0008
  - Directional light: intensity 0.3, position [5, 3, 5]
  - Ambient light: intensity 0.1

Language columns: 6 vertical floating typographic pillars in 3D space:
  - Slight arc arrangement, staggered Z-axis depth
  - Font size: 3.5vw desktop / 6vw tablet / 9vw mobile
  - Default state: opacity 0.4, letter-spacing 0.15em

Center element:
  - Thin horizontal rule, 1px, 60% width
  - Pulsing opacity animation (0.2 to 0.6, 3s ease-in-out infinite)
  - ACE monogram above (32px, wide tracking)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HOVER INTERACTION (desktop)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

On mouse enter:
  1. Opacity: 0.4 to 1.0 (200ms ease-out)
  2. Letter-spacing: 0.15em to 0.45em (300ms ease-out)
  3. Point light repositions toward hovered element (400ms)
  4. All other columns: opacity to 0.15 (200ms)
  5. Nearby particles drift toward cursor (physics)
  6. Micro-tone (50ms fade-in, max volume 0.08):
       en: 440Hz (A4)
       es: 528Hz (C5)
       fr: 396Hz (G4)
       zh: 639Hz (Eb5)
       ja: 741Hz (F#5)
       ko: 852Hz (Ab5)

On mouse leave:
  All elements return to default state (300ms ease-in)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TOUCH INTERACTION (mobile/tablet)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Tap activates hover state for 400ms then triggers selection.
Language columns in 2x3 grid on mobile.
Minimum touch target: 52x52px (Apple HIG compliance).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
THE SHATTER TRANSITION
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Duration: 900ms total.

Phase 1 (0–200ms):
  - Selected language scales to 200%, letter-spacing explodes
  - All other languages: opacity to 0, translateY(-20px)

Phase 2 (200–600ms):
  - Canvas fractures: 48 triangular fragments (desktop) / 24 (mobile)
  - Each fragment: random rotation, translateX/Y, scale 1->0, opacity 1->0
  - Implementation: Canvas 2D API + CSS transforms
  - Fragment explosion from click/tap origin point

Phase 3 (600–900ms):
  - Black void fills screen
  - MainApp fades in from opacity 0

After transition:
  - locale stored in IdentityContext and localStorage
  - Font architecture rewrites for selected language
  - document.documentElement lang attribute updates
  - Portal unmounts cleanly (GPU memory freed)

MOBILE PERFORMANCE FALLBACK:
  navigator.hardwareConcurrency < 4:
    Use CSS clip-path dissolve instead of fragment shatter.
    Canvas fades to black over 600ms with scale(1.05) push.

