━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XVII — SECTION 5: 3D AUDIO-REACTIVE MESH
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TECHNOLOGY: React Three Fiber + custom GLSL vertex shader + Web Audio API.

GEOMETRY: BufferGeometry sphere:
  Desktop: 8000 particles, radius 2.5
  Tablet:  4000 particles, radius 2.5
  Mobile:  2000 particles, radius 2.5
  Detection: window.innerWidth breakpoints

RENDERING: THREE.Points with ShaderMaterial.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
IDLE STATE (no audio)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  - Perfect sphere with slight random displacement
  - Breathing: uniform scale 0.95 to 1.05, 4s ease-in-out loop
  - Slow Y-axis rotation: 0.0005 rad/frame
  - Particle color: accent-color at 35% opacity
  - Particle size: 0.015 uniform
  - Fog: exponential, density 0.15

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ACTIVE STATE (audio playing)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  AudioContext.createAnalyser():
    fftSize: 2048 desktop/tablet, 512 mobile
    smoothingTimeConstant: 0.85
    getByteFrequencyData() -> Uint8Array(1024)

  Frequency band mapping:
    Bass  (0–10):    bassLevel — vertex displacement magnitude
    Mid   (10–100):  midLevel  — particle spread radius
    High  (100–512): highLevel — shimmer/sparkle speed
    Sub-bass peak:   triggers mesh deformation wave pulse

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GLSL VERTEX SHADER (exact code — verbatim)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  uniform float uTime;
  uniform float uBassLevel;
  uniform float uMidLevel;
  uniform float uHighLevel;
  uniform float uAudioData[128];
  attribute float aScale;

  void main() {
    vec3 pos = position;
    float noise = sin(pos.x * 8.0 + uTime * 0.5) *
                  cos(pos.y * 8.0 + uTime * 0.3) *
                  sin(pos.z * 8.0 + uTime * 0.4);
    float displacement = uBassLevel * 0.4 * noise;
    float spread = 1.0 + uMidLevel * 0.3;
    pos = pos * spread + normalize(pos) * displacement;
    vec4 mvPosition = modelViewMatrix * vec4(pos, 1.0);
    gl_Position = projectionMatrix * mvPosition;
    gl_PointSize = aScale * (uHighLevel * 3.0 + 1.5) *
                   (1.0 / -mvPosition.z);
  }

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GLSL FRAGMENT SHADER (exact code — verbatim)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  uniform vec3 uColor;
  uniform float uOpacity;

  void main() {
    float dist = distance(gl_PointCoord, vec2(0.5));
    if (dist > 0.5) discard;
    float alpha = 1.0 - (dist * 2.0);
    gl_FragColor = vec4(uColor, alpha * uOpacity);
  }

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
COLOR DYNAMICS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  bassLevel < 0.3:     accent-color at 35% opacity
  bassLevel 0.3–0.7:   interpolate accent to white
  bassLevel > 0.7:     pure white flash (20ms) then decay

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GPU MEMORY GUARD (mandatory on unmount — exact pattern)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  useEffect(() => {
    return () => {
      geometry.dispose();
      material.dispose();
      renderer.dispose();
    };
  }, []);

SUSPENSE WRAPPER: <Suspense fallback={<MeshSkeletonLoader />}>

INTERSECTION OBSERVER:
  Canvas animates only when in viewport.
  Off-screen: pause requestAnimationFrame loop.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XVIII — SECTION 6: PERSISTENT GLASSMORPHISM AUDIO PLAYER
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ARCHITECTURE LAW:
  AudioContext singleton lives in the root-level React context provider.
  The player component is purely presentational — reads state only, never
  owns state. This is the only architecture that guarantees zero audio
  dropout across all navigation.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VISUAL SPECIFICATIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Position:   fixed, bottom: 0, left: 0, right: 0
  z-index:    9999
  Height:     72px desktop / 56px mobile

  Background:
    backdrop-filter: blur(40px) saturate(200%) brightness(0.8)
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(40px) saturate(200%) brightness(0.8)
    background: rgba(var(--surface-rgb), 0.55)
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color)

  Vibrant integration on track change:
    box-shadow: 0 -4px 40px rgba([dominantColor], 0.15)
    Transition: 800ms ease

  Desktop layout: [Cover Art 52px] [Track Info] [Waveform flex-1] [Controls] [Volume]

  Mobile layout:
    Row 1: [Cover Art 36px] [Track Info] [Play/Pause]
    Row 2: [Waveform full-width]
    Collapsed: 56px — tap to expand to 120px

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
WAVEFORM RENDERER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Canvas: 100% width, 40px height
  Rendering: requestAnimationFrame at 60fps
  Data: analyser.getFloatTimeDomainData(dataArray)

  Drawing algorithm (exact):
    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, width, height)
    ctx.beginPath()
    for each sample:
      x = (i / bufferLength) * width
      y = (sample * 0.8 + 0.5) * height
      i === 0 ? ctx.moveTo(x, y) : ctx.lineTo(x, y)
    ctx.strokeStyle = dominantVibrantColor || accentColor
    ctx.lineWidth = 1.5
    ctx.stroke()

  Playhead: 1px vertical line at currentTime/duration ratio.
    Color: accent-color. Height: 100%. Width: 1px.
  Null-safe: renders flat centerline when no audio.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BROWSER AUTOPLAY COMPLIANCE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  AudioContext initialized ONLY after first user gesture.
  All play attempts before gesture: queued and executed on first gesture.
  Suspended AudioContext: resume() on user interaction.
  iOS Safari: handled via touchstart/click gesture detector.
  All play attempts: audioContext.resume().then(() => audioEl.play())

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VIBRANT.JS COLOR EXTRACTION — on every track change
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1. Load cover art image
  2. Vibrant.from(imageUrl).getPalette()
  3. Extract: Vibrant, Muted, DarkVibrant, DarkMuted
  4. Update CSS --dynamic-accent live
  5. Waveform color -> Vibrant swatch
  6. Player glow -> DarkMuted swatch
  7. Transition: 800ms ease on all color changes
  NOTE: If extracted hue is within 30 degrees of theme accent: desaturate.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XIX — SECTION 7: SPATIAL SCROLL ENGINE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HORIZONTAL TIMELINE (desktop + tablet)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Trigger: vertical scroll reaches 40% of viewport height.

  Mechanism:
    - Framer Motion useScroll({ target: containerRef })
    - useTransform(scrollYProgress, [0.4, 1.0], ['0%', '-80%'])
    - Applied to: transform: translateX() — hardware accelerated
    - FORBIDDEN: scrollLeft (causes layout repaints)
    - REQUIRED: will-change: transform on the scrolling container

  Snap behavior:
    scroll-snap-type: x mandatory
    scroll-snap-align: start per item
    scroll-snap-stop: always

  Timeline items (from IdentityContext.projects):
    Null safe: if projects is null, section renders as elegant empty strip.
    Item fields: title, year, type, description, cover image.
    Item width: 60vw desktop / 80vw tablet.

  Text mask reveal (scroll-linked):
    Achievement keyword at 120% scroll progress:
      font-size: 4rem to 24vw
      mix-blend-mode: difference
    Background video plays through text (heroVideo)
    Null-safe: gradient fallback if no video injected.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MOBILE ADAPTATION
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Horizontal scroll converts to standard vertical scroll.
  Timeline items stack vertically.
  Text mask: simplified to scale + opacity reveal.
  Touch swipe: Framer Motion drag constraints.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XX — SECTION 8: LIVE DOUBLE EXPOSURE PORTRAIT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Canvas blend engine — zero external libraries.

NULL STATE:
  portrait is null:
    ONYX/CYBER: pure black canvas.
    MINIMAL:    pure ivory canvas.

LAYER ARCHITECTURE:
  Layer 1 (base): composer portrait from IdentityContext
    - Drawn at full resolution
    - ONYX:    dark contrast boost
    - CYBER:   cyan tint overlay pre-applied
    - MINIMAL: desaturated (grayscale 100%)

  Layer 2 (overlay): procedurally generated music motifs
    All elements generated programmatically (no image files):
      - Staff lines (5-line musical staves)
      - Treble clef outlines
      - Piano keyboard silhouettes
      - Sinusoidal waveform curves
      - Eighth and quarter note shapes
      - Frequency bar visualizations
      - Vinyl groove spiral paths
    - Animation: elements pulse at track BPM
    - BPM null fallback: 80 BPM default
    - Motif scale oscillates ±8% at tempo
    - Motif opacity increases with bassLevel

BLEND MODES:
  ONYX:    ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'multiply'
             Motif: gold (#D4AF37) stroke lines
  CYBER:   ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'screen'
             Motif: cyan (#00F5D4) neon lines with glow
  MINIMAL: ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'overlay'
             Motif: dark (#1A1A18) precise lines

ANIMATION LOOP:
  requestAnimationFrame drives all motif animations.
  BPM-synced pulse: scale oscillates ±8% at tempo.
  Audio-reactive: motif opacity increases with bassLevel from AudioContext.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXI — SECTION 9: AI MEDIA PIPELINE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TRIGGER: Admin drops WAV/MP3 or pastes YouTube URL into the drop zone.
All processes run in PARALLEL via Promise.allSettled() for maximum resilience.
Raw Promise.all() is forbidden.

ERROR HANDLING LAW:
  Exponential backoff retry (max 3 attempts, delays: 1s, 2s, 4s) on all
  external API calls. On permanent failure after 3 retries: log to error state,
  preserve all successful outputs, gracefully degrade UI.
  The main thread MUST NEVER crash.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PROCESS 1 — AUDIO ANALYSIS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Library: music-metadata (npm)
  YouTube: youtube-dl-exec for metadata + thumbnail extraction
  Extract: bpm (music-tempo), mood, dominant instrument, key signature,
           duration, ID3 title tag
  Output: AudioMetadata stored in PipelineContext

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PROCESS 2 — AI VISUAL ART GENERATION
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  API: AI_IMAGE_GENERATION_KEY -> OpenAI DALL-E 3

  Cinematic prompt construction from AudioMetadata (exact text):
    "Photorealistic cinematic artwork.
     ${mood} atmosphere.
     ${dominantInstrument} as central visual metaphor.
     Shot on Phase One IQ4 medium format sensor.
     85mm f/1.4 lens, razor-thin depth of field.
     2200K warm-white key light with cold rim lighting.
     Aspect ratio 16:9. Dramatic shadow gradients.
     Color grade: ${themeColorGrade}.
     No text, no watermarks, no people's faces.
     Ultra-high detail, award-winning composition."

  Apply site theme color filter via Canvas API.
  Extract Vibrant palette from result. Generate BlurHash.
  Store in AWS S3: /tracks/{trackId}/cover.webp
  Returns: MediaAsset with all fields populated.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PROCESS 3 — POLYGLOT SONIC NARRATOR
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  API: LLM_NARRATIVE_API_KEY -> OpenAI GPT-4o

  LLM prompt (exact text):
    "You are the world's most celebrated music journalist writing liner
     notes for an Academy Award-winning composer's portfolio.
     Audio metadata: ${JSON.stringify(audioMetadata)}
     Write a captivating dramatic narrative for this piece.
     Tone: cinematic, sophisticated, emotionally resonant.
     Length: 2-3 sentences per language.
     Output ONLY this JSON, no markdown, no preamble:
     { en: '', es: '', fr: '', zh: '', ja: '', ko: '' }"

  REQUIRED: response_format: { type: "json_object" } in OpenAI SDK call.
  Response parsed and validated as MultiLingual interface.
  Store in tracks table.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PROCESS 4 — PLAYLIST MANAGEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  YouTube URL:
    youtube-dl-exec extracts: title, duration, thumbnail, channel.
    Site visual style rendered over thumbnail via Canvas API.
    Added to playlist at bottom (default sort_order).

  Drag-and-drop reordering:
    @dnd-kit/sortable with DndContext.
    onDragEnd: PUT /api/tracks/reorder with new sort_order array.
    Optimistic UI update + API confirmation.
    Smooth reorder transition: 300ms ease.

  APPROVAL GATE:
    Generated art and narrative shown to admin before publishing.
    Admin can edit any narrative field in any language.
    Admin can regenerate art or narrative independently.
    Track goes live (is_live = true) ONLY after "Approve & Publish".

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXII — SECTION 10: EXECUTIVE STUDIO BOT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

POSITION: fixed, bottom: 88px (above audio player), right: 24px
z-index: 9998
Trigger: circular floating button, 56px diameter, accent-color

OPEN STATE: panel slides up (Framer Motion spring)
  Desktop: 380px wide, 520px tall, glassmorphism, border-radius: 16px
  Mobile: 100vw, 70vh, full-screen bottom sheet

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CAPABILITIES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  1. Responds in visitor's selected locale exclusively
  2. Portfolio semantic search: mood, genre, tempo, instrument queries
  3. Inline audio player inside chat messages (global AudioContext)
  4. Structured project brief intake collector
  5. Brief submission: POST /api/briefs

MULTILINGUAL SYSTEM PROMPT (exact text):
  "You are the Executive Studio Manager for a world-class international
   composer. You speak ${locale} fluently and exclusively. Your tone is
   professional, cinematic, warm.
   Composer portfolio: ${JSON.stringify(tracks)}
   When recommending tracks, include the track ID for inline player.
   When asked for a project brief, collect in this order:
     1. Media type (film / game / animation / documentary / commercial)
     2. Emotional direction (3 keywords)
     3. Budget range (below $5k / $5k-$25k / $25k-$100k / above $100k)
     4. Deadline
   Then confirm and submit via POST /api/briefs."

INLINE PLAYER IN CHAT:
  Bot message includes: { type: 'track_recommendation', trackId: string }
  Frontend renders PersistentAudioPlayer mini-variant inside chat bubble.
  Connects to global AudioContext — zero new audio instances.

BRIEF SUBMISSION:
  POST /api/briefs with structured data.
  Admin dashboard shows unread brief indicator.
  Optional SMTP email notification via configured SMTP.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXIII — SECTION 11: GOD-MODE ADMIN DASHBOARD
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ACCESS METHOD 1: Ctrl+Shift+A (desktop keyboard shortcut)
ACCESS METHOD 2: /admin route (requires Gatekeeper auth)
ACCESS METHOD 3: Triple-tap ACE logo in footer (mobile)

GATEKEEPER AUTHENTICATION:
  Username + password -> bcrypt hash comparison (cost factor: 12)
  Access JWT: 24h expiry, httpOnly cookie, SameSite=strict
  Refresh JWT: 30-day rolling, httpOnly cookie
  Failed attempts: 5 max -> 15-minute lockout
  Lockout state: stored in admin_users.failed_attempts + locked_until
  Zero third-party auth services.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TAB 1 — IDENTITY MATRIX
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Multilingual fields (6-language sub-tabs EN|ES|FR|ZH|JA|KO):
    - Full Name
    - Artistic Tagline
    - Biography (rich text, markdown support)
    - Awards & Recognition (repeatable array with +/- controls)
    - Studio Address

