────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TAB 4 — STAGING ENGINE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Edit Mode / Live Mode toggle at top of panel.

  Edit Mode:
    - Blue dashed borders on all injectable components
    - Click text -> inline edit activates
    - Click image -> file picker opens
    - Changes accumulate in StagingContext (draft only, not live)
    - Unsaved indicator: orange dot on tab label

  Preview panels (simultaneous):
    - Three panels: ONYX | CYBER | MINIMAL
    - Viewport selector: Mobile (375px) | Tablet (768px) | Desktop (1440px)

  Approve & Publish:
    - Diff view: staged changes vs live state
    - Atomic commit: all changes go live simultaneously
    - Rollback: revert to previous live state (stored in staging_drafts)

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TAB 5 — CMS DOCUMENT ASSISTANT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Upload zone: PDF, .txt, .eml files.

  AI processing via LLM_NARRATIVE_API_KEY:
    Extract: timecodes, revision notes, delivery requirements, deadlines.
    Output: structured checklist grouped by:
      Timecodes | Revisions | Deliverables | Deadlines
    Each item: checkbox, priority indicator, due date if found.

  Export as PDF: POST /api/documents/export
  Send to email: POST /api/documents/email (via configured SMTP)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXIV — SECTION 12: GRID LAYOUT RANDOMIZATION ENGINE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Selected on page load via seeded random, persisted for session.
Framer Motion stagger entrance on all variants.
All variants are null-safe.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VARIANT A — BILLBOARD FULL BLEED
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Hero: 100vw x 100vh full-bleed portrait or pure black canvas (null-safe)
  Text overlay: bottom-left, large serif
    Name:    clamp(3rem, 8vw, 9rem), var(--font-display)
    Tagline: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.5rem), var(--font-body), opacity 0.7
  Scroll indicator: thin pulsing vertical line, right side
  Audio player: slides from bottom on first scroll
  CTA: "Enter Studio" button, centered at 70% vh
  Mobile: center-aligned text, portrait fills 60vh top

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VARIANT B — ASYMMETRIC EDITORIAL GRID
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  CSS Grid: repeat(12, 1fr), gap: 0, 100vh height
  Portrait: columns 1-7, rows 1-4 (bleed left edge)
  Name + tagline: columns 8-12, rows 1-2
    Name: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 6rem)
  Bio excerpt: columns 8-12, row 3 (max 3 lines with ellipsis)
  Track count + genre badges: columns 8-12, row 4
  Audio player card: columns 8-12, rows 5-6 (glassmorphism)
  All grid areas null-safe: empty -> pure surface-color
  Mobile: single column, portrait top (50vh), content below

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VARIANT C — DECONSTRUCTED TYPOGRAPHIC
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Composer name: 18vw-25vw, deliberately overflows viewport
  Letterforms: positioned as CSS Grid structural elements
  Content flows in negative space between letterforms
  Portrait: inside letterform void (clip-path mask)
  Scroll: letters separate (translateX) revealing content behind
    Framer Motion useTransform on scrollYProgress
    Separation: 0% to ±15vw over full scroll range
  Mobile: name at 45vw, single-column stacked below

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXV — SECTION 13: RESPONSIVE & CROSS-PLATFORM STANDARDS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ZERO HORIZONTAL OVERFLOW LAW (CRITICAL):
  The agent MUST guarantee that at exactly 375px, 768px, and 1440px viewport
  widths, there is strictly 0px of horizontal scrolling. All containers MUST
  use CSS overflow-x: hidden at the root wrapper, and internal CSS grids and
  flexboxes must be strictly mathematically bounded to a maximum of 100vw.

BREAKPOINTS:
  xs: 320px - 479px    (small phones)
  sm: 480px - 767px    (large phones)
  md: 768px - 1023px   (tablets)
  lg: 1024px - 1439px  (laptops)
  xl: 1440px - 1919px  (desktops)
  2xl: 1920px+         (4K displays)

PLATFORM TARGETS:
  iOS Safari (iPhone 12+)
  Android Chrome (Android 10+)
  macOS Safari + Chrome + Firefox
  Windows Chrome + Edge + Firefox
  iPadOS (landscape and portrait)
  4K displays (1920px+)

MOBILE-SPECIFIC ADAPTATIONS:
  Linguistic Portal: 2x3 grid, touch targets min 52px
  3D Mesh: 2000 particles, fftSize 512
  Audio Player: collapsed bottom sheet, swipe up to expand to 120px
  Spatial Scroll: vertical layout, Framer Motion swipe gestures
  Admin Dashboard: bottom tab bar, full-screen panels
  Studio Bot: full-screen bottom sheet
  Grid layouts: all 3 variants -> single-column stacked

iOS SAFARI REQUIREMENTS:
  AudioContext: deferred until touchstart/click
  Viewport: dvh units everywhere (not vh)
  Prefix: -webkit-backdrop-filter always included
  Scroll momentum: -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch
  Safe areas: env(safe-area-inset-*) on all fixed elements
  Input zoom prevention: font-size minimum 16px on all inputs

ANDROID CHROME REQUIREMENTS:
  Hardware back button: close modals/panels before navigation
  Touch feedback: ripple on all interactive elements
  Overscroll: overscroll-behavior: contain on all scroll containers
  Viewport: 100dvh not 100vh

PERFORMANCE TARGETS:
  Lighthouse Performance: >= 90 (all devices)
  Lighthouse Accessibility: >= 95
  Lighthouse Best Practices: >= 95
  Lighthouse SEO: >= 90
  First Contentful Paint: < 1.2s
  Largest Contentful Paint: < 2.5s
  Cumulative Layout Shift: < 0.1
  Time to Interactive: < 3.0s

PERFORMANCE TECHNIQUES:
  Images: WebP format, BlurHash placeholders, lazy loading
  3D Canvas: IntersectionObserver pause when off-screen
  Code splitting: React.lazy() for all major components
  Bundle warning threshold: 200KB per chunk
  Fonts: preloaded in <head>, font-display: swap
  Animations: CSS transforms only (no layout-triggering properties)
  React.memo: all expensive pure components

ACCESSIBILITY:
  prefers-reduced-motion: all non-essential animations disabled
  Focus indicators: 2px solid accent-color, 2px offset
  ARIA labels: all icon-only buttons
  ARIA live regions: dynamic content announcements
  Color contrast: WCAG AA minimum (4.5:1 body text)
  Semantic HTML: nav, main, section, article, header, footer
  Keyboard navigation: all interactive elements fully accessible
  Skip navigation link: visible on focus
  CJK typography: font-feature-settings for correct character rendering

CJK TYPOGRAPHY RULES:
  Korean: word-break: keep-all
  Chinese: word-break: break-all disabled
  Japanese: line-break: strict, font-feature-settings: "palt" 1
  All CJK: text-align: justify disabled, overflow-wrap: break-word
  All text: clamp() for responsive scaling — no pixel-locked font sizes

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXVI — SECTION 14: API ARCHITECTURE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

BASE URL:
  Development: http://localhost:8080
  Production:  https://api.ace-2026.com

SPEC: OpenAPI 3.0 at lib/api-spec/openapi.yaml (source of truth)
All routes MUST match the OpenAPI spec exactly.
CORS: frontend origin only — wildcard (*) forbidden.
RATE LIMITING: 100 req/min per IP (express-rate-limit + Redis store).
HELMET: full security headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options).
COMPRESSION: gzip on all text responses.

S3 CORS LAW:
  All S3 media tag references MUST include crossorigin="anonymous".
  S3 bucket CORS policy MUST explicitly allow GET from frontend origin.
  This prevents tainted canvas errors in WebGL and Canvas API operations.

STAGING PREVIEW PAYLOAD:
  POST /api/media/staging-preview:
    Accepts multipart/form-data.
    Processes file in temporary memory buffer.
    Returns: temporary Signed URL + Vibrant palette + audio duration.
    MUST NOT permanently store the file.

STANDARD RESPONSE ENVELOPE:
  interface ApiResponse<T> {
    success: boolean;
    data: T | null;
    error: string | null;
    code: string | null;
    timestamp: string;
  }

COMPLETE ROUTE MANIFEST:
  POST /api/auth/login
  POST /api/auth/logout
  POST /api/auth/refresh
  GET  /api/identity
  PUT  /api/identity
  POST /api/identity/translate
  POST /api/media/upload
  POST /api/media/staging-preview
  POST /api/pipeline/process
  GET  /api/pipeline/status/:jobId
  POST /api/pipeline/approve/:jobId
  POST /api/pipeline/regenerate/:jobId
  GET  /api/tracks
  POST /api/tracks
  PUT  /api/tracks/:id
  DELETE /api/tracks/:id
  PUT  /api/tracks/reorder
  GET  /api/tracks/:id/stream
  GET  /api/briefs
  POST /api/briefs
  POST /api/keys
  GET  /api/keys/status
  POST /api/keys/test
  POST /api/chat
  POST /api/documents/analyze
  POST /api/documents/export
  POST /api/documents/email
  GET  /api/health
  GET  /api/admin/queue-dashboard    (JWT protected)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXVII — SECTION 15: DATABASE SCHEMA (PostgreSQL 16 + Drizzle ORM)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

DRIZZLE ORM LAWS:
  - Explicit relations() defined for every table association.
  - ON DELETE CASCADE on all foreign keys.
  - B-Tree indexes on all searchable fields and foreign keys.
  - All tables: gen_random_uuid() primary keys.
  - All JSONB fields: default '{}' not null.
  - All timestamps: TIMESTAMPTZ (timezone-aware).

DATABASE MIGRATION LAWS:
  - Migrations are immutable once generated.
  - Every schema change requires a new migration file.
  - Historical migrations MUST NEVER be edited.
  - Migration ordering MUST remain deterministic.
  - Rollback scripts MUST exist for every migration.
  - Seed scripts MUST NEVER contain demo or fake content.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TABLE DEFINITIONS (COMPLETE)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

TABLE: composer_identity
  id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  name            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  tagline         JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  biography       JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  awards          JSONB[] NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  studio_address  JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  portrait_url    TEXT
  portrait_blur   TEXT
  logo_url        TEXT
  hero_video_url  TEXT
  social_links    JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()

TABLE: projects
  id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  composer_id     UUID REFERENCES composer_identity(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
  title           JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  type            TEXT NOT NULL
  year            INTEGER
  description     JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  cover_url       TEXT
  cover_blur      TEXT
  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()

TABLE: tracks
  id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  title           JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  narrative       JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  audio_url       TEXT
  cover_url       TEXT
  cover_blur      TEXT
  dominant_colors TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}'
  vibrant_palette JSONB
  genre           TEXT
  bpm             INTEGER
  mood            TEXT
  key_signature   TEXT
  duration        INTEGER
  sort_order      INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
  is_live         BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()

TABLE: pipeline_jobs
  id                   UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  track_id             UUID REFERENCES tracks(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
  status               TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'idle'
  progress             INTEGER DEFAULT 0
  audio_metadata       JSONB
  generated_art_url    TEXT
  generated_narrative  JSONB
  error_message        TEXT
  created_at           TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
  updated_at           TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()

TABLE: api_keys
  id               UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  key_name         TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL
  encrypted_value  TEXT NOT NULL
  iv               TEXT NOT NULL
  auth_tag         TEXT NOT NULL
  is_active        BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
  tested_at        TIMESTAMPTZ
  updated_at       TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()

TABLE: admin_users
  id               UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  username         TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL
  password_hash    TEXT NOT NULL
  failed_attempts  INTEGER DEFAULT 0
  locked_until     TIMESTAMPTZ
  last_login       TIMESTAMPTZ
  created_at       TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()

TABLE: briefs
  id                  UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  locale              TEXT NOT NULL
  budget_range        TEXT
  media_type          TEXT
  deadline            TEXT
  emotional_direction TEXT
  raw_conversation    JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  is_read             BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()

TABLE: staging_drafts
  id           UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
  entity_type  TEXT NOT NULL
  entity_id    UUID
  draft_data   JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
  created_by   UUID REFERENCES admin_users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL
  created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
B-TREE INDEXES (MANDATORY — ALL MUST BE CREATED)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  CREATE INDEX idx_projects_composer_id      ON projects(composer_id);
  CREATE INDEX idx_pipeline_jobs_track_id    ON pipeline_jobs(track_id);
  CREATE INDEX idx_tracks_sort_order         ON tracks(sort_order);
  CREATE INDEX idx_tracks_is_live            ON tracks(is_live);
  CREATE INDEX idx_briefs_is_read            ON briefs(is_read);
  CREATE INDEX idx_api_keys_key_name         ON api_keys(key_name);
  CREATE INDEX idx_staging_drafts_entity_id  ON staging_drafts(entity_id);

