PART XXVIII — SECTION 16: CREATIVE DIRECTION & VISUAL DNA
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

VISUAL REFERENCES:
  Apple.com product pages         — spatial depth, typography precision
  Porsche.com                     — performance aesthetics, black space, metallic restraint
  Teenage Engineering             — industrial minimalism
  NASA mission control            — data density + visual clarity
  Kubrick film frame compositions — mathematical precision in framing

MOTION DESIGN PRINCIPLES:
  Every entrance animation has purpose — not decoration.
  Physics-based springs for interactive elements.
  Cinematic easing: cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94)
  No linear animations.
  Stagger delays on lists: 0.05s between items.
  Exit animations always present — nothing disappears instantly.
  Loading states are always resolved states, never bare spinners.
  Error states are visually precise, never raw console messages.

TYPOGRAPHY PRINCIPLES:
  Scale creates hierarchy, not weight alone.
  Whitespace is content.
  Text never competes with imagery.
  CJK: respect character spacing, never force-track.
  Responsive type: clamp() everywhere — no pixel-locked sizes.

COLOR PRINCIPLES:
  One accent color maximum per theme.
  Accent used sparingly (maximum 10% of visible surface).
  Vibrant.js colors MUST NOT clash with theme accent.
  If extracted hue is within 30 degrees of accent: desaturate.
  WCAG AA minimum on all text/background combinations.

INTERACTION PRINCIPLES:
  Every interactive element: feedback within 50ms.
  Hover states begin animating on cursor approach.
  Touch targets minimum 44x44px (Apple HIG), 52x52px critical elements.

[OMNI-STATE MAGNETIC CURSOR SYSTEM]
  - Custom global cursor bypassing OS pointer (cursor: none).
  - Default: 12px solid dot, mix-blend-mode: exclusion.
  - Hover states: expands/morphs based on target:
      Text  -> line
      Media -> circle with 'VIEW'
      Audio -> circle with 'PLAY'
  - Magnetic Physics: cursor snaps to center of interactive buttons via
    Framer Motion spring (stiffness 150).
  - MUST gracefully hide on touch devices:
    window.matchMedia('(pointer: coarse)')

