PART XXXIII — SUPPLEMENTARY COMPONENT SPECIFICATIONS
(Additional components referenced throughout the blueprint)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PIPELINE CONTEXT — artifacts/ace-2026/src/context/PipelineContext.tsx
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Manages the full state machine for AI pipeline jobs.
  States: idle | uploading | analyzing_audio | generating_art |
          generating_narrative | applying_filters | awaiting_approval |
          publishing | complete | error
  All transitions driven by SSE events from /api/pipeline/status/:jobId.
  Must expose: currentJob, jobHistory, startJob(), cancelJob(), resetJob().
  All consumers receive strongly typed PipelineJob data.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STAGING CONTEXT — artifacts/ace-2026/src/context/StagingContext.tsx
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Manages draft vs live mode toggle.
  draftState: all staged changes (not yet committed).
  liveState: currently published data.
  isEditMode: boolean.
  hasPendingChanges: boolean (drives orange dot indicator on tab).
  commitDraft(): atomic commit of all staged changes.
  rollbackDraft(): revert to previous live state.
  All draft data accumulates locally before commit — zero API calls during editing.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GRID LAYOUT ENGINE — artifacts/ace-2026/src/components/GridLayoutEngine.tsx
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Selects layout variant on page load: Math.random() seeded for session.
  Persists selected variant in sessionStorage (NOT localStorage — per-session).
  Renders Variant A, B, or C based on selection.
  All three variants must be present in the same file as conditional renders.
  Framer Motion AnimatePresence wraps each variant's content blocks.
  staggerChildren: 0.05s on all list-like content within variants.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DOUBLE EXPOSURE PORTRAIT — artifacts/ace-2026/src/components/DoubleExposurePortrait.tsx
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Full spec in Section 8 above.
  Canvas size: matches container dimensions via ResizeObserver.
  AudioContext integration: reads bassLevel from useAudioReactive hook.
  BPM sync: if currentTrack.bpm is null, default to 80 BPM.
  All music motifs drawn with ctx.beginPath() / ctx.stroke() — zero image assets.
  On unmount: cancelAnimationFrame(), canvas context cleared.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STAGING PREVIEW — artifacts/ace-2026/src/components/StagingPreview.tsx
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Renders three simultaneous iframes or scaled-down panels:
    ONYX (dark) | CYBER (cyber) | MINIMAL (light)
  Each panel has its own isolated theme variable scope.
  Viewport selector buttons above: Mobile (375px) | Tablet (768px) | Desktop (1440px)
  Each panel scales to fit within the admin panel viewport.
  Shows draft state data, not live state.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VIBRANT EXTRACTOR — artifacts/ace-2026/src/lib/vibrantExtractor.ts
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  extractPalette(imageUrl: string): Promise<VibrantPalette | null>
  Uses Vibrant.from(imageUrl).getPalette()
  Maps Vibrant swatches to VibrantPalette interface
  Hue clash detection: if Math.abs(extractedHue - themeAccentHue) < 30 degrees:
    desaturate extracted color by 60%
  Returns null on failure (logged, non-crashing)
  Used by: AudioContext (on track change), aiArtGenerator, PersistentAudioPlayer

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
THEME ENGINE — artifacts/ace-2026/src/lib/themeEngine.ts
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Exports: THEMES: ThemeConfig[] (all 3 theme objects with exact CSS variables)
  selectRandomTheme(): ThemeId — uses Math.random(), persists to localStorage
  getStoredTheme(): ThemeId | null
  applyTheme(themeId: ThemeId, locale: Locale): void — direct DOM injection
  All theme variable maps must be 100% complete — no partial theme objects

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LOCALE ENGINE — artifacts/ace-2026/src/lib/localeEngine.ts
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  getInitialLocale(): Locale — checks localStorage, then navigator.language
  setLocale(locale: Locale): void — stores in localStorage
  getLocalizedText(content: MultiLingual | null, locale: Locale): string
    Returns empty string '' when content is null (never throws)
  applyLocaleTypography(locale: Locale, theme: ThemeConfig): void
    Injects all typography CSS variables for the given locale/theme combo

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXXIV — CONTEXT PROVIDER HIERARCHY & NESTING ORDER
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The provider nesting order in main.tsx is MANDATORY and IMMUTABLE.
No provider may be reordered without explicit instruction.
Order (outermost to innermost):

  1. ChromaticProvider        — must be outermost (theme before everything)
  2. IdentityProvider         — composer data + locale (depends on theme)
  3. AudioProvider            — audio singleton (depends on identity for tracks)
  4. PipelineProvider         — AI pipeline state (depends on audio context)
  5. StagingProvider          — staging/draft system (depends on identity)
  [Children / Router / Pages]

Exact structure in main.tsx:
  <ChromaticProvider>
    <IdentityProvider>
      <AudioProvider>
        <PipelineProvider>
          <StagingProvider>
            <App />
          </StagingProvider>
        </PipelineProvider>
      </AudioProvider>
    </IdentityProvider>
  </ChromaticProvider>

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXXV — ERROR BOUNDARY ARCHITECTURE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

React Error Boundaries REQUIRED at the following levels:
  1. Root level (wraps entire app) — shows full-screen dark error panel
  2. Route level (per page/section) — shows section-scoped fallback
  3. AudioReactiveMesh (WebGL canvas) — shows static particle image fallback
  4. LiquidImage (WebGL planes) — falls back to standard <img> tag
  5. LinguisticPortal (Three.js scene) — falls back to static 2D version
  6. All async data regions (identity, tracks, pipeline) — shows loading/empty states

Error boundary fallback components:
  - NEVER show raw error messages to users
  - ONYX/CYBER: dark canvas with minimal accent-colored text
  - MINIMAL: ivory canvas with muted text
  - Log errors to console with timestamp + module source
  - In production: send to error tracking service endpoint

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXXVI — DEMO MODE ISOLATION ARCHITECTURE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

When DEMO_MODE=true (environment variable):

FRONTEND DEMO ROUTING:
  - All audio requests → /public/audio/[filename]
  - All image requests → /public/images/[filename]
  - All video requests → /public/videos/[filename]
  - API calls → local mock controllers (no real HTTP requests)

BACKEND DEMO ROUTING:
  - Database writes: intercepted, logged, not committed
  - AI API calls: intercepted, simulated with local mock data
  - File uploads: stored in temp memory, not persisted to S3

DEMO OFFLINE UI BADGE:
  Fixed position indicator: "DEMO MODE" in top-right corner
  Styling: accent-color border, surface background, 12px monospace font
  Not visible in production (DEMO_MODE=false removes it from DOM)

MOCK DATA REQUIREMENTS:
  - All mock data uses the full 6-language schema: { en, es, fr, zh, ja, ko }
  - Mock tracks include: id, title (multilingual), audioUrl (/public/audio/),
    coverArt with blurHash, genre, bpm, mood, duration, isLive: true
  - Simulated AI processing delay: 1500ms-2500ms (randomized)
  - Mock responses match exact ApiResponse<T> envelope structure

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
