    - PipelineJob
    - AudioMetadata
    - Brief
  paths: (all 27 routes from Section 14 fully documented)
  security schemes: bearerAuth (JWT via httpOnly cookie)

All route definitions must include:
  - requestBody schema
  - response schema (200, 400, 401, 403, 500)
  - security requirements
  - example payloads

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXXVIII — PERFORMANCE BUDGET & BUNDLE CONSTRAINTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

BUNDLE SIZE LIMITS:
  - Per chunk warning threshold: 200KB
  - Initial JS bundle (main): < 150KB gzipped
  - Three.js chunk (lazy): < 300KB gzipped
  - Framer Motion chunk (lazy): < 80KB gzipped
  - Admin dashboard chunk (lazy, code-split): < 200KB gzipped

LAZY LOADING STRATEGY (React.lazy() required for):
  - LinguisticPortal (Three.js dependency)
  - AudioReactiveMesh (Three.js dependency)
  - AdminDashboard (all 5 tabs, heavy UI)
  - ExecutiveStudioBot (AI-dependent)
  - DoubleExposurePortrait (canvas-heavy)

CRITICAL RENDER PATH:
  - Only ChromaticContext and root shell rendered synchronously
  - All heavy components behind Suspense with BlurHash/skeleton fallbacks
  - No blocking resources in index.html (all fonts preloaded, not blocking)

VITE BUILD CONFIGURATION:
  - rollupOptions.output.manualChunks for Three.js, Framer Motion, admin
  - build.chunkSizeWarningLimit: 200
  - build.sourcemap: false in production
  - build.minify: 'esbuild'
  - build.target: 'es2020'

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PART XXXIX — SECURITY IMPLEMENTATION CHECKLIST
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Backend Security (all must be present in artifacts/api-server/src/index.ts):
  [ ] helmet() with full CSP header configuration
  [ ] cors({ origin: process.env.FRONTEND_URL }) — no wildcard
  [ ] express-rate-limit with RedisStore (100 req/min)
  [ ] compression() middleware for gzip
  [ ] express.json({ limit: '10mb' }) body size limit
  [ ] morgan('combined') for access logging (dev only)
  [ ] Global error handler middleware (last in chain)
  [ ] process.on('unhandledRejection') and process.on('uncaughtException')
  [ ] Zod validation middleware factory for all routes
  [ ] JWT verification middleware protecting all admin routes
  [ ] CSRF token generation and validation
  [ ] Secure cookie configuration (httpOnly, sameSite: 'strict', secure: prod)
  [ ] SQL injection prevention via Drizzle parameterized queries only
  [ ] XSS sanitization on all user-submitted text fields
  [ ] AES-256-GCM encryption for all stored API keys
  [ ] bcrypt with cost factor 12 for password hashing
  [ ] Failed login attempt tracking with 15-minute lockout at 5 failures
  [ ] No stack traces in production error responses
  [ ] No secrets in logs, error messages, or API responses
  [ ] S3 presigned URLs with expiry for all media delivery

Frontend Security:
  [ ] No API keys in frontend code or localStorage
  [ ] All admin inputs type="password" for sensitive fields
  [ ] CSP meta tag matching server Helmet CSP
  [ ] Subresource integrity (sri) for all CDN resources
  [ ] No eval() usage anywhere in the codebase
  [ ] All external links: rel="noopener noreferrer"

